data.description: Charm meets potential in this Columbia, PA gem! Formerly an old railroad rooming house, this 123+ year old brick home boasts character and history. The third floor, not included in the total square footage, adds extra space for your imagination. With a newer roof, solar panels, and recently updated kitchen featuring new cabinets and granite counters, this fixer-upper offers a blend of old-world allure and modern touches. Front and back staircases, a side balcony, and first-floor laundry add to the appeal. Cosmetic repairs await, but envision the possibilities in this unique property!
